---
title: Honey-Glazed Pork Tenderloin with Sweet Potatoes and Green Beans
description: A honey glaze may sound like something that goes with dessert, but mild-tasting pork loves a sweet sauce too, especially one that has a few savory elements in it for contrast. In this recipe, you’ll be folding an extra-large drizzle of honey into a rich, savory pan sauce, then spooning it onto pork tenderloin (and the roasted sweet potatoes and green beans, if you like).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5b03336d30006c14c65229f2-be4b353b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/honey-glazed-pork-tenderloin-5b03336d30006c14c65229f2-ef0ab6bd.pdf
cuisine: North America
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/honey-glazed-pork-tenderloin-5b03336d30006c14c65229f2
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 540 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 480 mg
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Peel @sweet potatoes{2} and cut into ½-inch cubes. Toss on one half of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until tender, ~{20-25%minutes} total (we'll check in after ~{10%minutes}).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @pork tenderloin{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook in pan, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{6-8%minutes}. While pork cooks, mince @garlic{1%clove} (use the other as you like). Strip @thyme{2%tsp} leaves from @thyme{1/4%ounce}(stems stripped).

After sweet potatoes have roasted ~{10%minutes}, remove from oven and toss, keeping toward one side of baking sheet. Add @green beans{6%ounce} to other side and toss with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Return baking sheet to oven and roast until both veggies are tender, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Once pork is browned, transfer to another baking sheet. Roast in oven to desired doneness, ~{8-12%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add garlic and thyme. Cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @water{1/4%cup}, and @honey{1/2%ounce}. Scrape up any browned bits on bottom of pan. Simmer until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add @butter{1%tablespoon} and stir to melt. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: If glaze seems stiff, stir in a splash or two of water.

Let pork rest ~{2-3%minutes} after removing from oven, then thinly slice. Divide green beans and sweet potatoes between plates, then top with pork. Drizzle with glaze and serve.